Description: numpy\_ringbuffer
        =================
        
        |Build Status| |codecov|
        
        Ring (aka circular) buffers backed by a numpy array, supporting:
        
        -  Operations from ``collections.deque``
        -  ``b.append(val)``
        -  ``b.appendleft(val)``
        -  ``b.extend(val)``
        -  ``b.extendleft(val)``
        -  ``b.pop(val)``
        -  ``b.popleft(val)``
        -  The ``collections.Sequence`` protocol (unoptimized)
        -  C-side unwrapping into an array with ``np.array(b)``
        -  Arbitrary element dtypes, including extra dimensions like
           ``RingBuffer(N, dtype=(int, 3))``
        
        For example:
        
        .. code:: python
        
            import numpy as np
            from numpy_ringbuffer import RingBuffer
        
            r = RingBuffer(capacity=4, dtype=np.bool)
            r.append(True)
            r.appendleft(False)
            print(np.array(r))  # array([False, True])
        
        .. |Build Status| image:: https://travis-ci.org/eric-wieser/numpy_ringbuffer.svg?branch=master
